# Toyota Connected India – Internal Vision-Language Prototype

This repository contains internal tooling and research code for Vision-Language model experimentation at **Toyota Connected India**. It integrates open-source projects under permitted licenses, enabling real-time perception capabilities on mobile and embedded devices.

> **Internal Use Only**  
This project is intended **strictly for Toyota Connected India employees** for non-commercial, research, or prototyping purposes. Redistribution or external publication must comply with third-party license terms below.

---

## Acknowledgements & Third-Party Licenses

Portions of this software utilize components licensed from the following projects. We gratefully acknowledge the authors and contributors of these works.

---

### [LLaVA](https://github.com/haotian-liu/LLaVA) – Large Language and Vision Assistant

**License**: Apache License 2.0  
**Source**: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

> Used for multimodal input processing combining vision and language understanding.

---

### [FastViT (ml-fastvit)](https://github.com/apple/ml-fastvit) – Apple Inc.

**License**: Apple Software License  
**Copyright**: © 2023 Apple Inc.

> Enables efficient vision transformer inference on Apple Silicon devices.

---

### [mlx-vlm](https://github.com/apple/ml-macos) – Apple Inc.

**License**: MIT License  
**Copyright**: © 2023 Apple Inc.

> Supports lightweight vision-language models and multimodal inference workflows.

---

### [MobileCLIP (ml-mobileclip)](https://github.com/apple/ml-mobileclip) – Apple Inc.

**License**: MIT License  
**Copyright**: © 2024 Apple Inc.

> Used for efficient visual embedding and mobile deployment.  
Model weights and data licenses available in `LICENSE_weights_data` and `ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS`.

